The paper proposes an unsupervised learning approach for simultaneous sample and feature selection, which is a common problem in machine learning and can be applied to various sub-fields such as computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and data mining (cs.DS). The proposed method involves active learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of matrix decomposition, which is a common technique in signal processing (cs.SP) and information theory (cs.IT). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, and cs.SI (for the use of matrix decomposition).
